%I A179586 #22 Jul 22 2026 08:23:50
%S A179586 23964880,181202031,1279247260,8518503575,54074432712,330241565427,
%T A179586 1954955180610,11285043586569,63824872040196,355002589996908,
%U A179586 1947739374558590,10566515438382830,56790441671512256,302860151119528226,1604673062447407780,8455931307028544910,44354581274461912472
%N A179586 Number of permutations of 1..n+11 with deficiencies #{i: p(i) < i} exceeding the exceedances #{i: p(i) > i} by n or more.
%C A179586 The sequence satisfies a linear recurrence of order 30, and has an OGF with denominator (1 - x)^10*(1 - 2*x)^8*(1 - 3*x)^6*(1 - 4*x)^4*(1 - 5*x)^2. - _M. F. Hasler_, Jul 18 2026
%H A179586 M. F. Hasler and R. J. Mathar, <a href="/A179582/a179582_3.pdf">Hardin's exceedance excesses A179579-A179582</a>, July 2026.
%H A179586 <a href="/index/Rec#order_30">Index to entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, order 30.
%F A179586 a(n) = 5^(n + 10)*(n + 16) + 4^(n + 8)*((n + 11)*(n^2 - 89*n - 1470)/6) + 3^(n + 5)*((n + 10)*(n + 11)*(n^3 - 201*n^2 + 2846*n + 68544)/40) + 2^n*((n + 9)*(n + 10)*(n + 11)*(n^4 - 212*n^3 + 7853*n^2 + 64598*n - 461328)/315) + (n + 8)*(n + 9)*(n + 10)*(n + 11)*(n^5 - 110*n^4 + 2315*n^3 + 17330*n^2 - 199296*n - 927360)/362880. - _M. F. Hasler_, Jul 18 2026
%F A179586 a(n) = A179585(n+1)+A179578(n). - _R. J. Mathar_, Jul 22 2026
%o A179586 (PARI) \\ The explicit formula for a(n) is valid PARI/GP code. - _M. F. Hasler_, Jul 18 2026
%o A179586 (Python) # See the Hasler-Mathar link for Python code that gives the explicit formula.
%Y A179586 Cf. A179579 ([n+4]), A179580 ([n+5]), A179581 ([n+6]), A179582 ([n+7]), A179583 ([n+8]), A179584 ([n+9]), A179585 ([n+10]).
%Y A179586 Cf. A179571 - A179578 (similar with excess exactly n), A179566 - A179570 (fixed minimum excess), A179564 - A179565 (fixed exact excess).
%K A179586 nonn,easy,changed
%O A179586 0,1
%A A179586 _R. H. Hardin_, Jul 19 2010
